The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                               The City Diary
                A 23-year-old man, arrested on the charge of theft, hanged himself in the Alipore police station lock-up on Sunday afternoon. Police said Shambhu Das, who lived in an Alipore shanty and had been arrested several times earlier, was addicted to narcotics and had been showing withdrawal symptoms. He took off his trousers and hanged himself with it after being denied narcotics, said an officer. Relatives of Das vandalised the police station at night, alleging that he died because of police torture.     A 42-year-old motorcyclist was crushed by a CSTC bus at the Belvedere Road-AJC Bose Road crossing on Sunday afternoon. Taimur Ali, a resident of Ekbalpore, was taken to SSKM Hospital, where he was declared dead. Police said Taimur rammed into a bus while riding his bike at a high speed and fell on the road. The CSTC bus, which was right behind the bike, ran him over.     Two persons were killed after the car they were travelling in was hit by a truck at the Kanpa crossing in Barrackpore on Sunday. Police said Tapas Pal, 30, and his neighbour Rinku Samadder, 25, were returning home after visiting a friend at Kalyani when the truck hit them from the front. The two were taken to Jawaharlal Nehru Hospital in Kalyani, where they were declared dead. The truck was impounded but the driver and his help fled.    Two men died on Sunday afternoon after consuming hooch in an illegal liquor den in Bishnupur. Three other men also fell ill after drinking in the den and were admitted to a local hospital. The den owner fled.    A 35-year-old woman was arrested in a Birati house on Sunday for allegedly being involved in a trafficking racket. Jharna Kar was behind the disappearance of Soma Das, a student of Class IX in a Birati school, on June 14, said police. Soma was traced to a hotel in Haldia on Saturday night after her family got a tip-off from some youths close to Jharna. Local residents handed her over to the police.     A passenger was not allowed to board a Dubai-bound Emirates flight at the city airport on Sunday evening because he was allegedly drunk. S.C. Ghosh, a Behala resident who works in a Dubai-based company, was stopped by airline officials after clearing immigration.    A 44-year-old cancer patient died on a Mumbai-Howrah train on his way to Howrah on Saturday. Police said Sanjay Nag, a resident of Yogdharma in Howrah, went to Mumbai a week ago for treatment.    An unidentified man in his 40s died at RG Kar Hospital late on Saturday after being hit by a car on Cossipore Road on Friday night.    Avijeet Paul and Raju Sarkar, in their early thirties, were arrested in Salt Lake on Sunday night in connection with a land fraud case. Police said the duo worked in a Tiljala-based construction firm that had sold forms for ownership of apartments at New Town in Rajarhat. The forms, priced at Rs 200 each, asked for immediate payment of an instalment, which aroused the suspicion of prospective buyers. We checked records and found that the firm had not registered the plot in its name and had no authority to sell such forms, said a police officer.     A gang threw crude bombs near an iron factory on Makardah Road in Howrah on Sunday morning.             
